File: The entire stadium erupted, as the Glamour Boys moved ten points clear of their nearest rivals Mamelodi Sundowns. JOHANNESBURG - Kaizer Chiefs beat Golden arrows 1-0 at the Moses Mabhida stadium on Saturday. The win sees the table-topping Glamour Boys move ten points clear of their nearest rivals Mamelodi Sundowns. Steve Komphela's side seemed to be holding Chiefs to a draw until Lebogang Manyana fired home a dramatic winner in the 93rd minute. Chiefs sit comfortably atop the Absa Premiership table (45pts) with Sundowns in 2nd (35pts) with a game in hand.